1
00:00:02.319 --> 00:00:04.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. A little lower.

2
00:00:05.957 --> 00:00:06.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lower.

3
00:00:07.996 --> 00:00:08.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lower.

4
00:00:08.877 --> 00:00:09.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs softly )

5
00:00:11.316 --> 00:00:12.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's that?

6
00:00:12.675 --> 00:00:13.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

7
00:00:15.634 --> 00:00:18.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ODO: Well, I hope this taught
you a lesson.

8
00:00:18.553 --> 00:00:19.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

9
00:00:19.833 --> 00:00:23.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Never play spring ball
against a changeling.

10
00:00:23.832 --> 00:00:26.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, just for that, next time,

11
00:00:26.671 --> 00:00:29.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not going
to let you win a single game.

12
00:00:29.471 --> 00:00:32.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then you'd better work
on your backhand.

13
00:00:32.549 --> 00:00:33.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-mm.

14
00:00:34.428 --> 00:00:37.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Right now, all I want to do is just sleep
for two or three--

15
00:00:37.668 --> 00:00:39.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping ) oh, oh, oh...

16
00:00:39.667 --> 00:00:40.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Days.

17
00:00:41.146 --> 00:00:42.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go right ahead.

18
00:00:43.269 --> 00:00:45.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should be back by the time you wake up.

19
00:00:45.825 --> 00:00:47.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Back? From where?

20
00:00:47.905 --> 00:00:51.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I received a coded message
from Gul Russol this morning.

21
00:00:52.303 --> 00:00:53.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gul Russol.

22
00:00:55.262 --> 00:00:58.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought he was executed
when Cardassia joined the Dominion.

23
00:00:58.662 --> 00:01:03.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So did I, but apparently we were wrong.
The message says he wants to meet with me.

24
00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why?
-I don't know,

25
00:01:05.739 --> 00:01:08.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but he's my most reliable
Cardassian informant.

26
00:01:08.938 --> 00:01:13.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean he was. What if Russol is dead
and this is just a trap?

27
00:01:13.177 --> 00:01:15.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've thought about that,
but I have to be sure.

28
00:01:16.166 --> 00:01:17.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I owe him that much.

29
00:01:19.735 --> 00:01:22.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Want me to come with you?
-Russol insists I come alone.

30
00:01:25.534 --> 00:01:28.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Nerys.
I'll be careful.

31
00:01:29.332 --> 00:01:31.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worried? Ha.

32
00:01:31.572 --> 00:01:34.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This just gives me more time to work
on my backhand.

33
00:01:34.291 --> 00:01:35.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

34
00:01:42.487 --> 00:01:43.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Chief!

35
00:01:43.648 --> 00:01:46.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How much longer is the Promenade
going to be closed?

36
00:01:47.327 --> 00:01:49.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My bar is empty. My waiters are bored.

37
00:01:50.466 --> 00:01:52.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-And I'm losing money.
-Leave me alone, Quark,

38
00:01:52.925 --> 00:01:55.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or I'll feed you to one
of those plasma conductors.

39
00:01:55.364 --> 00:01:58.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you threatening me?
-We're working as fast as we can.

40
00:01:59.323 --> 00:02:03.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As spokesman for the Promenade
Merchants' Association, I'm going to file

41
00:02:03.282 --> 00:02:07.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-an official protest with Captain Sisko.
-Put it in writing, Quark.

42
00:02:07.881 --> 00:02:09.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll go find a padd.

43
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:13.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how much longer, Chief?

44
00:02:14.797 --> 00:02:16.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, we should be through here
by the end of the day, sir.

45
00:02:16.598 --> 00:02:19.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I'm not talking about the Promenade.
I'm talking about the <i>Defiant.</i>

46
00:02:19.717 --> 00:02:21.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When is the gravity net
going to be repaired?

47
00:02:21.877 --> 00:02:24.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The last time I stepped onto the Bridge,
I felt ten kilos heavier.

48
00:02:25.235 --> 00:02:29.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'm afraid it's going to take some time.
-How much time? About three weeks.

49
00:02:29.234 --> 00:02:31.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to replace
the graviton stabilizer.

50
00:02:31.714 --> 00:02:34.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have three days. I'm going to take
the <i>Defiant </i>back out on patrol,

51
00:02:34.952 --> 00:02:39.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I don't want my crew getting queasy
because the gravity keeps fluctuating.

52
00:02:39.432 --> 00:02:41.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But, sir, the Sector Quartermaster said,

53
00:02:41.351 --> 00:02:44.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it would take three weeks
to get us a new stabilizer.

54
00:02:44.430 --> 00:02:46.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that is your problem, Chief.

55
00:02:46.629 --> 00:02:48.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, I'm leaving for Bajor
for a conference,

56
00:02:48.508 --> 00:02:52.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I want that stabilizer replaced
by the time I get back.

57
00:02:52.588 --> 00:02:53.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do I make myself clear?

58
00:02:53.627 --> 00:02:54.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

59
00:02:58.664 --> 00:03:00.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't mean to sound negative,
but I don't see

60
00:03:00.505 --> 00:03:02.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how you're going to get the <i>Defiant</i>
ready in three days.

61
00:03:02.305 --> 00:03:03.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Neither do I.

62
00:03:06.783 --> 00:03:09.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This Quartermaster you've been dealing
with, what's his name?

63
00:03:10.302 --> 00:03:13.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, Chief... Chief... Chief Willoughby.

64
00:03:13.781 --> 00:03:15.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean his first name. I don't know.

65
00:03:16.260 --> 00:03:17.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is he married?
-Married?

66
00:03:18.602 --> 00:03:20.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What does that have to do with getting
us a graviton stabilizer?

67
00:03:20.858 --> 00:03:22.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything. This Chief Willoughby

68
00:03:22.738 --> 00:03:25.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
must get hundreds of supply requisitions
every day.

69
00:03:25.657 --> 00:03:29.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He can't possibly fill them all.
So he puts everyone on a waiting list.

70
00:03:29.177 --> 00:03:32.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know how he feels.
I do the same thing.

71
00:03:32.975 --> 00:03:35.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, the secret is getting him to put you

72
00:03:35.454 --> 00:03:37.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
at the top of that list,
and the best way to do that

73
00:03:37.814 --> 00:03:39.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is to form a relationship with him.

74
00:03:39.893 --> 00:03:42.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
NOG: Get to know the name of his wife,
his children.

75
00:03:43.252 --> 00:03:45.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Find out what he likes to eat.

76
00:03:45.131 --> 00:03:48.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't have time to form
a relationship with Willoughby.

77
00:03:50.210 --> 00:03:51.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do.

78
00:03:52.210 --> 00:03:54.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can get you that stabilizer, Chief.

79
00:03:54.849 --> 00:03:57.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In three days? Leave everything to me.

80
00:03:58.866 --> 00:04:00.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right. But don't do anything
I wouldn't do.

81
00:04:00.967 --> 00:04:03.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, I can't operate
under those kinds of restrictions.

82
00:04:04.366 --> 00:04:07.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least promise me you won't do anything
to get us court-martialed.

83
00:04:10.448 --> 00:04:11.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll try.
-Nog!

84
00:04:12.438 --> 00:04:13.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just kidding, Chief.

85
00:04:13.403 --> 00:04:14.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

86
00:04:14.443 --> 00:04:16.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

87
00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:37.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Russol?

88
00:04:41.835 --> 00:04:44.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Russol?
-WEYOUN: I'm afraid he couldn't be here.

89
00:04:48.728 --> 00:04:49.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Weyoun.

90
00:04:53.392 --> 00:04:54.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Founder.

91
00:04:55.311 --> 00:04:58.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is an honor to stand
in your presence once again.

92
00:04:59.270 --> 00:05:00.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where's Gul Russol?

93
00:05:01.294 --> 00:05:05.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid the Cardassian Central Command
had him put to death almost a year ago.

94
00:05:05.947 --> 00:05:08.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN: I regret having to deceive you,

95
00:05:08.386 --> 00:05:10.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it was the only way I could
think of to get you here.

96
00:05:10.866 --> 00:05:13.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm here.
What do you want?

97
00:05:14.545 --> 00:05:15.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To serve you.

98
00:05:17.704 --> 00:05:20.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I no longer consider myself
a member of the Dominion.

99
00:05:22.863 --> 00:05:24.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're defecting?

100
00:05:25.422 --> 00:05:26.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do with me as you wish.

101
00:05:28.181 --> 00:05:30.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I place my fate entirely in your hands.

102
00:07:28.344 --> 00:07:29.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't believe me, do you?

103
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:33.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I believe Gul Russol is dead.

104
00:07:34.637 --> 00:07:37.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You say you're defecting
from the Dominion? Why?

105
00:07:38.618 --> 00:07:41.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Founder, please...
-I've told you before, I'm not a Founder.

106
00:07:41.981 --> 00:07:42.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
As you wish.

107
00:07:44.860 --> 00:07:49.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Odo... I'll tell you
everything you want to know, but first,

108
00:07:49.989 --> 00:07:51.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
we really should get aboard your runabout.

109
00:07:51.979 --> 00:07:53.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Jem'Hadar are already hunting for me,
and if I'm found--

110
00:07:53.977 --> 00:07:56.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You still haven't answered my question.

111
00:07:59.775 --> 00:08:02.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Why did you decide to defect?

112
00:08:02.934 --> 00:08:04.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I realized my place is with you.

113
00:08:05.614 --> 00:08:07.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You can do better than that.

114
00:08:09.928 --> 00:08:13.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Then let's just say, I left Cardassia
because my life was in danger.

115
00:08:14.530 --> 00:08:16.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-From whom?
-Everyone.

116
00:08:17.907 --> 00:08:18.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Aren't you being a little paranoid?

117
00:08:19.504 --> 00:08:21.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Of course, I'm paranoid, everyone's trying
to kill me.

118
00:08:21.209 --> 00:08:23.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Why?
-Because this war with the Federation

119
00:08:23.648 --> 00:08:25.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
was supposed to have been won months ago.

120
00:08:26.247 --> 00:08:28.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, things don't always
turn out as planned.

121
00:08:28.727 --> 00:08:32.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Quite true... and when things go wrong,
someone has to take the blame

122
00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:33.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and this time, it's me.

123
00:08:34.605 --> 00:08:37.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Now...
we really should be going.

124
00:08:42.122 --> 00:08:47.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Think about it, Odo.
The information I possess

125
00:08:47.881 --> 00:08:50.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
could help the Federation win this war.

126
00:08:51.200 --> 00:08:54.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And you're willing
to share that information?

127
00:08:54.679 --> 00:08:55.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
All you have to do is ask.

128
00:08:58.997 --> 00:09:01.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We've heard rumors
that the Dominion has established

129
00:09:01.637 --> 00:09:06.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
a new ketracel-white storage facility
somewhere in sector 507.

130
00:09:07.275 --> 00:09:08.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The facility's located
in the Pelosa system.

131
00:09:08.994 --> 00:09:11.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can provide you
with the exact coordinates.

132
00:09:15.673 --> 00:09:17.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo to the <i>Rio Grande,</i> two to beam up.

133
00:09:17.912 --> 00:09:19.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

134
00:09:26.299 --> 00:09:28.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sit here, where I can keep an eye on you.

135
00:09:29.629 --> 00:09:31.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it makes you feel better...

136
00:09:31.988 --> 00:09:34.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you should know
I would never harm a God.

137
00:09:34.667 --> 00:09:37.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not a God. I'm a security officer.

138
00:09:37.266 --> 00:09:39.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As far as I'm concerned,
you're just another prisoner.

139
00:09:40.904 --> 00:09:44.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have no idea how much
it hurts me to hear you say that.

140
00:09:44.424 --> 00:09:45.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

141
00:09:53.461 --> 00:09:55.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I spoke to Edgar.
-Edgar who?

142
00:09:55.501 --> 00:09:57.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your new best friend,
Chief Edgar Willoughby.

143
00:09:57.940 --> 00:10:01.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He wanted me to thank you for that bottle
of Gamzian wine you sent him.

144
00:10:02.298 --> 00:10:05.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I didn't send him any wine.
-I took the liberty of sending it for you.

145
00:10:05.378 --> 00:10:09.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By the way, his wife's name is Cynthia.
They have a daughter, Melissa, age eight,

146
00:10:09.657 --> 00:10:12.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-and a son, Edgar Jr., age five.
-Did you get the stabilizer?

147
00:10:12.816 --> 00:10:14.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Not quite.
-What do you mean, "not quite"?

148
00:10:14.575 --> 00:10:16.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unfortunately, he's out of stabilizers

149
00:10:16.414 --> 00:10:18.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and won't be getting a new shipment
for another week.

150
00:10:18.213 --> 00:10:19.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, well, that's it, I'm doomed.

151
00:10:19.814 --> 00:10:23.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not necessarily. Eddie told me
the USS <i>Sentinel</i> has an extra stabilizer.

152
00:10:24.527 --> 00:10:25.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What makes you think
they're going to give it to us?

153
00:10:49.779 --> 00:11:05.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't say they were going
to give it to us...

154
00:10:28.516 --> 00:10:29.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but they might be willing to trade for it.

155
00:10:29.571 --> 00:10:31.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trade? For what?

156
00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:33.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Depends on what they need
and what we have.

157
00:10:34.489 --> 00:10:39.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I suppose it doesn't hurt to try.
But remember, be discreet.

158
00:10:39.767 --> 00:10:41.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rule of Acquisition 168,

159
00:10:42.206 --> 00:10:43.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Whisper your way to success."

160
00:10:43.967 --> 00:10:45.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckling ) Words to live by.

161
00:10:45.686 --> 00:10:48.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, one more thing.
I need your authorization code.

162
00:11:25.139 --> 00:11:36.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What for?
-The shipping orders.

163
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:42.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bring them to me and I'll authorize them.

164
00:10:53.435 --> 00:10:54.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just thought it would save time.

165
00:11:09.437 --> 00:11:10.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When did you say the Captain
was going to be back?

166
00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:00.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

167
00:11:05.620 --> 00:11:09.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Stop looking so worried, Chief.
I've got it all under control.

168
00:10:58.331 --> 00:10:59.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I sure hope so.

169
00:11:08.727 --> 00:11:10.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish you'd stop doing that.

170
00:11:10.727 --> 00:11:12.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Doing what?
-Staring at me.

171
00:11:12.647 --> 00:11:14.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was I? I didn't mean to.

172
00:11:14.966 --> 00:11:16.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've been doing it
for the last ten hours.

173
00:11:16.645 --> 00:11:20.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry.
It's just such an honor to be sitting here

174
00:11:20.284 --> 00:11:21.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with a G--

175
00:11:22.323 --> 00:11:23.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Security officer.

176
00:11:25.041 --> 00:11:25.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

177
00:11:41.717 --> 00:11:43.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're being hailed.
-WEYOUN: Don't respond.

178
00:11:46.315 --> 00:11:48.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's a Cardassian transmission.
-Scramble the com frequencies

179
00:11:43.976 --> 00:11:46.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-So they can't lock onto us.
-I'm trying.

180
00:11:36.819 --> 00:11:41.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Founder... it's an honor to speak </i>
<i>with you again.</i>

181
00:11:48.956 --> 00:11:53.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-You look surprised to see me, Odo.</i>
-I'm well aware the Vorta are all clones,

182
00:11:54.034 --> 00:11:57.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I'm not sure the universe
is ready for two Weyouns.

183
00:11:57.473 --> 00:11:59.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I couldn't agree more.</i>

184
00:11:59.792 --> 00:12:03.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, which of you is the Weyoun

185
00:12:03.311 --> 00:12:06.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've had the misfortune of dealing
with over the past few years?

186
00:12:06.671 --> 00:12:07.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually, neither of us.

187
00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:13.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That was Weyoun 5. Our illustrious </i>
<i>predecessor</i> <i>was killed a month ago.</i>

188
00:12:14.548 --> 00:12:16.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I had the honor of replacing him.

189
00:12:16.907 --> 00:12:22.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>What a sad day that was for the Dominion.</i>
<i>Weyoun 5 was a great man, a true patriot.</i>

190
00:12:22.905 --> 00:12:27.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His death in a transporter...
accident was most unfortunate.

191
00:12:27.624 --> 00:12:30.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN 6: <i>And still under investigation.</i>

192
00:12:30.703 --> 00:12:34.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A very thorough investigation
that has found no evidence of foul play.

193
00:12:34.381 --> 00:12:35.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Interesting.

194
00:12:36.181 --> 00:12:40.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, if you're Weyoun 6, you must be 7.

195
00:12:40.460 --> 00:12:43.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Clones, keeping track
of them is a full-time job.

196
00:12:44.179 --> 00:12:47.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And why were you activated
if he's still alive?

197
00:12:47.458 --> 00:12:50.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Normally, I wouldn't have been, but when
a clone is found to be defective...

198
00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:52.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'm not defective.
-WEYOUN 7: <i>Of course you are.</i>

199
00:12:53.017 --> 00:12:55.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What other explanation is there
for your behavior?

200
00:12:55.416 --> 00:12:57.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leaving your post, defecting to the enemy.

201
00:12:57.615 --> 00:13:00.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you calling Odo your enemy?
<i>-Absolutely not.</i>

202
00:13:00.174 --> 00:13:03.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was referring to the Federation,
as you're well aware.

203
00:13:03.333 --> 00:13:06.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Enough bickering. Order him to trigger
his implant.

204
00:13:06.812 --> 00:13:08.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was getting to that.

205
00:13:09.860 --> 00:13:10.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What implant?

206
00:13:10.491 --> 00:13:11.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like all Vorta,

207
00:13:11.891 --> 00:13:14.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a termination implant
in my brain stem.

208
00:13:14.330 --> 00:13:17.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prove your loyalty
to the Founders activate it.

209
00:13:17.649 --> 00:13:21.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only Founder I'm loyal to is Odo,
and he wants me alive.

210
00:13:21.168 --> 00:13:24.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I told you it was a waste of time</i>
<i>trying to reason with him.</i>

211
00:13:24.647 --> 00:13:27.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're a dead man</i>
<i>whether you activate the implant or not.</i>

212
00:13:27.566 --> 00:13:29.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That ship will never make it back </i>
<i>to Deep Space 9.</i>

213
00:13:30.685 --> 00:13:32.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Founder, there's really no need</i>

214
00:13:32.765 --> 00:13:35.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>for you to be involved</i>
<i>in this petty dispute.</i>

215
00:13:35.244 --> 00:13:38.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If you'll just hold your position</i>
<i>until one of our ships can reach you.</i>

216
00:13:38.363 --> 00:13:41.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have no intention of releasing
my prisoner to you.

217
00:13:41.642 --> 00:13:42.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN 7: <i>If you don't,</i>

218
00:13:42.561 --> 00:13:44.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can't be responsible </i>
<i>for the consequences.</i>

219
00:13:44.481 --> 00:13:47.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's an empty threat.
He wouldn't dare harm a Founder.

220
00:13:47.800 --> 00:13:50.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe he won't, but I will.

221
00:13:51.359 --> 00:13:54.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Think it over, shape-shifter.</i>
<i>One of our attack ships is on the way.</i>

222
00:14:04.715 --> 00:14:05.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forgive me, Odo.

223
00:14:06.474 --> 00:14:08.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should have told you
the truth about myself.

224
00:14:08.554 --> 00:14:10.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's not too late to start.

225
00:14:12.312 --> 00:14:13.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did you defect?

226
00:14:15.832 --> 00:14:17.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's quite simple really.

227
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:22.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From the moment I was activated,
I felt this war was wrong.

228
00:14:22.749 --> 00:14:27.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please don't misunderstand me.
I still worship the Founders,

229
00:14:26.229 --> 00:14:27.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I believe their obsession

230
00:14:28.028 --> 00:14:31.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with conquering the Alpha
Quadrant is misguided.

231
00:14:31.466 --> 00:14:34.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's time they learned to live in peace
with the solids.

232
00:14:35.506 --> 00:14:38.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know it's not my place
to question the Founders.

233
00:14:41.184 --> 00:14:43.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe Weyoun 7 is right.

234
00:14:44.743 --> 00:14:46.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am defective.

235
00:14:48.182 --> 00:14:49.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On the contrary.

236
00:14:49.501 --> 00:14:51.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What you're saying, about the war,

237
00:14:51.955 --> 00:14:52.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about the Founders...

238
00:14:53.980 --> 00:14:55.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Makes perfect sense.

239
00:14:58.218 --> 00:14:59.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to thank you, Odo

240
00:14:59.699 --> 00:15:02.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for the way you stood up for me,
protected me.

241
00:15:02.617 --> 00:15:03.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, don't let it go to your head.

242
00:15:04.656 --> 00:15:06.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd do the same for any prisoner.

243
00:15:06.855 --> 00:15:08.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course, you would.

244
00:15:08.696 --> 00:15:10.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're a God.

245
00:15:22.891 --> 00:15:28.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To think a Weyoun
could be capable of such treachery.

246
00:15:29.170 --> 00:15:31.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I knew there was something wrong with him
from the moment we met.

247
00:15:32.169 --> 00:15:33.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He lacked your appetite for cruelty.

248
00:15:34.048 --> 00:15:37.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a disgrace to me and all Vorta.

249
00:15:38.686 --> 00:15:44.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Though... I suppose he can't be held
completely responsible for his behavior.

250
00:15:45.205 --> 00:15:48.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Vorta cloning process
is a very delicate one.

251
00:15:48.884 --> 00:15:53.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every once in a while, a clone is found
to be defective.

252
00:15:53.682 --> 00:15:57.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's never happened to a Weyoun before
but, it does happen.

253
00:15:58.481 --> 00:16:01.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And speaking of treachery...

254
00:16:02.799 --> 00:16:06.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there is still the little matter
of the death of Weyoun 5.

255
00:16:06.998 --> 00:16:08.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You really believe I had something
to do with that?

256
00:16:08.677 --> 00:16:10.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were supposed
to be on that transporter pad with him.

257
00:16:11.037 --> 00:16:12.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was called away, urgent meeting
with Central Command.

258
00:16:12.917 --> 00:16:14.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How convenient.

259
00:16:14.316 --> 00:16:16.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I always was lucky.
-Hmm.

260
00:16:17.235 --> 00:16:19.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you sure I can't interest you
in a glass of <i>kanar?</i>

261
00:16:20.714 --> 00:16:24.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid our problems won't be washed
away quite that easily.

262
00:16:24.953 --> 00:16:26.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know
what you're so concerned about.

263
00:16:26.552 --> 00:16:29.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo couldn't possibly hope to outrun
a Jem'Hadar attack ship.

264
00:16:29.657 --> 00:16:32.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if he refuses
to hand over his prisoner?

265
00:16:32.911 --> 00:16:33.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then he'll die.

266
00:16:34.230 --> 00:16:38.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He will not.
We can't kill a Founder. I forbid it.

267
00:16:39.232 --> 00:16:43.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unless we stop them, Odo is going to take
your predecessor back to the Federation

268
00:16:43.547 --> 00:16:45.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where he will undoubtedly
reveal all he knows,

269
00:16:45.426 --> 00:16:47.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all you know,
about our strategic operations.

270
00:16:48.025 --> 00:16:51.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You know what that means, don't you?
-It means we could lose the war.

271
00:16:52.345 --> 00:16:55.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right.
And I will not allow that to happen.

272
00:16:56.543 --> 00:16:58.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cardassia has risked too much,
suffered too much.

273
00:16:59.172 --> 00:17:01.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will not stand by
and let all of our plans,

274
00:17:01.222 --> 00:17:03.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all of our dreams
for the future end in defeat

275
00:17:03.941 --> 00:17:06.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just to spare the life
of one shape-shifter.

276
00:17:06.300 --> 00:17:08.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't believe the Jem'Hadar
are going to fire on Odo,

277
00:17:09.953 --> 00:17:10.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
even if they're ordered to.

278
00:17:12.259 --> 00:17:14.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They don't need to know he's on board.

279
00:17:15.737 --> 00:17:18.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You simply order them
to destroy the runabout.

280
00:17:21.656 --> 00:17:23.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose it could work.

281
00:17:23.895 --> 00:17:28.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if the Founders ever found out that we
were responsible for Odo's death...

282
00:17:28.454 --> 00:17:29.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's going to tell them?

283
00:17:35.864 --> 00:17:39.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo doesn't even consider himself
a Founder.

284
00:17:40.371 --> 00:17:41.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we agree.

285
00:17:42.810 --> 00:17:44.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The runabout must be destroyed.

286
00:17:50.207 --> 00:17:51.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excellent.

287
00:17:52.766 --> 00:17:55.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, I really think you
should try a little <i>kanar.</i>

288
00:18:09.162 --> 00:18:10.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

289
00:18:17.239 --> 00:18:20.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Morning, Lieutenant.
-I'd make myself scarce if I were you.

290
00:18:20.518 --> 00:18:22.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why?
-KIRA: Chief.

291
00:18:22.198 --> 00:18:23.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In here now.

292
00:18:24.797 --> 00:18:26.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tried to warn you.

293
00:18:33.035 --> 00:18:34.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you mind explaining this?

294
00:18:35.914 --> 00:18:38.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where's the Captain's desk?
-Oh, you don't know?

295
00:18:38.593 --> 00:18:40.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is your authorization code, isn't it?

296
00:18:41.672 --> 00:18:43.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nog.
-What about him?

297
00:18:45.351 --> 00:18:47.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He must have traded the Captain's desk

298
00:18:47.710 --> 00:18:49.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-for the graviton stabilizer.
-Excuse me?

299
00:18:50.030 --> 00:18:51.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Colonel.
I will get the desk back.

300
00:18:51.988 --> 00:18:53.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you're damn right, you will.

301
00:18:53.668 --> 00:18:55.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Captain is returning
from Bajor in two days,

302
00:18:56.227 --> 00:19:00.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and when he does, I want his desk
sitting right here, where it belongs.

303
00:19:01.226 --> 00:19:04.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Chief. I didn't give away
the Captain's desk.

304
00:19:04.225 --> 00:19:06.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I just loaned it to someone.
-Who?

305
00:19:06.264 --> 00:19:09.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Al Lorenzo.
-Who's Al Lorenzo?

306
00:19:09.980 --> 00:19:11.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Chief of Operations on Decos Prime.

307
00:19:11.543 --> 00:19:13.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does he want with the Captain's desk?

308
00:19:13.262 --> 00:19:15.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He wants to take a picture of it.

309
00:19:15.942 --> 00:19:16.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

310
00:19:16.902 --> 00:19:19.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He likes to collect holophotos of himself

311
00:19:19.260 --> 00:19:22.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
sitting behind the desks
of famous Starfleet Captains.

312
00:19:22.460 --> 00:19:24.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Usually, he just sneaks
into their offices,

313
00:19:24.419 --> 00:19:26.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but with the war on, it's been hard
for him to get away.

314
00:19:27.018 --> 00:19:28.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that makes sense.

315
00:19:28.658 --> 00:19:32.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's got quite a collection.
Captain DeSoto's desk, Captain Picard's--

316
00:19:32.497 --> 00:19:37.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, fine. So... once he has his picture,

317
00:19:37.895 --> 00:19:40.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he's going to send us
the graviton stabilizer.

318
00:19:40.733 --> 00:19:43.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. He's giving us an induction modulator.

319
00:19:43.173 --> 00:19:44.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we don't need an induction modulator.

320
00:19:45.013 --> 00:19:46.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But the USS <i>Musashi </i>does.

321
00:19:47.732 --> 00:19:48.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah...

322
00:19:48.812 --> 00:19:51.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so the <i>Musashi's </i>going
to send us the stabilizer.

323
00:19:51.651 --> 00:19:53.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. They're giving us a phaser emitter.

324
00:19:53.610 --> 00:19:55.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we don't need a phaser emitter.

325
00:19:55.770 --> 00:20:00.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know, but the USS <i>Sentinel </i>does,
and they have the extra stabilizer.

326
00:20:00.288 --> 00:20:02.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And they're willing to give
it up for a phaser emitter?

327
00:20:02.808 --> 00:20:04.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's the rumor.
-Rumor?

328
00:20:05.207 --> 00:20:07.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've made all these deals
based on a rumor?

329
00:20:07.766 --> 00:20:09.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
From a very reliable source.

330
00:20:09.845 --> 00:20:11.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, what if it turns out not to be true?

331
00:20:11.795 --> 00:20:12.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have to have faith, Chief.

332
00:20:12.925 --> 00:20:17.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-In a rumor?
-No. In the Great Material Continuum.

333
00:20:19.563 --> 00:20:20.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are they?

334
00:20:21.002 --> 00:20:25.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not a "they." It's the force
that binds the universe together.

335
00:20:25.600 --> 00:20:27.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must have missed that class
in engineering school.

336
00:20:28.040 --> 00:20:29.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
NOG: On Ferenginar, we learn about
the Continuum

337
00:20:29.879 --> 00:20:32.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
while we still have our first set of ears.

338
00:20:32.239 --> 00:20:34.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no time for Ferengi fairy tales.

339
00:20:34.838 --> 00:20:36.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Continuum is real.

340
00:20:39.316 --> 00:20:42.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see, there are millions
upon millions of worlds

341
00:20:43.035 --> 00:20:46.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the universe, each one filled
with too much of one thing

342
00:20:46.675 --> 00:20:48.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and not enough of another.

343
00:20:48.154 --> 00:20:50.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Great Continuum
flows through them all

344
00:20:50.953 --> 00:20:54.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
like a mighty river,
from have to want and back again.

345
00:20:55.032 --> 00:20:57.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And, if we navigate the Continuum

346
00:20:57.511 --> 00:20:59.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with skill and grace,

347
00:20:59.390 --> 00:21:02.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
our ship will be filled
with everything our hearts desire.

348
00:21:03.430 --> 00:21:04.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, right now,
I'd settle for a stabilizer

349
00:21:05.029 --> 00:21:06.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the Captain's desk.

350
00:21:08.828 --> 00:21:10.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The river will provide.

351
00:21:10.347 --> 00:21:12.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( scoffs ) If it doesn't sink us first.

352
00:21:18.025 --> 00:21:20.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( mumbling )

353
00:21:22.383 --> 00:21:23.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo?

354
00:21:26.342 --> 00:21:27.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

355
00:21:28.422 --> 00:21:31.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

356
00:21:31.558 --> 00:21:32.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

357
00:21:33.780 --> 00:21:36.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I was... dreaming.

358
00:21:38.219 --> 00:21:40.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sounded more like a nightmare.

359
00:21:42.618 --> 00:21:47.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was on Earth...
Starfleet Headquarters.

360
00:21:47.616 --> 00:21:53.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was supposed to report for my debriefing
but I couldn't find the right office.

361
00:21:54.654 --> 00:21:58.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I started calling your name,
but you didn't answer.

362
00:21:59.372 --> 00:22:03.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then suddenly...
I was being chased by some Jem'Hadar...

363
00:22:03.851 --> 00:22:06.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or were they Klingons?

364
00:22:07.490 --> 00:22:09.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

365
00:22:14.288 --> 00:22:15.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Silly, isn't it?

366
00:22:17.207 --> 00:22:18.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not at all.

367
00:22:19.487 --> 00:22:22.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It isn't easy to turn your back
on your own people.

368
00:22:23.805 --> 00:22:25.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Believe me, I know.

369
00:22:28.284 --> 00:22:31.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo, do you think Starfleet
would allow you

370
00:22:31.403 --> 00:22:33.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to conduct my debriefing?

371
00:22:37.521 --> 00:22:38.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Possibly.

372
00:22:40.840 --> 00:22:43.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It would make it much easier.

373
00:22:43.360 --> 00:22:44.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

374
00:22:44.439 --> 00:22:45.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( alarm blares )

375
00:22:45.559 --> 00:22:47.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it?
-Trouble.

376
00:23:04.193 --> 00:23:06.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe they're firing on us.

377
00:23:07.712 --> 00:23:08.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trust me, they are.

378
00:23:08.712 --> 00:23:11.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But the Jem'Hadar would never obey
an order to harm a Founder.

379
00:23:11.551 --> 00:23:14.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe they finally got it through
their head that I'm not a Founder.

380
00:23:15.430 --> 00:23:17.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or they don't know who they're firing at.

381
00:23:17.669 --> 00:23:19.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got to let them know
you're on board.

382
00:23:19.348 --> 00:23:21.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're jamming all the frequencies.
I can't get through.

383
00:23:22.308 --> 00:23:24.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've been ordered
not to communicate with us.

384
00:23:25.209 --> 00:23:28.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damar said he was determined
not to let us get back to the station.

385
00:23:32.344 --> 00:23:33.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See if you can get above them.

386
00:23:34.904 --> 00:23:35.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

387
00:23:35.783 --> 00:23:37.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll explain later. Just do it.

388
00:23:44.181 --> 00:23:45.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What now?

389
00:23:45.741 --> 00:23:47.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lock phasers on their dorsal
field junction.

390
00:23:47.860 --> 00:23:49.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their shields are weakest there.

391
00:24:03.856 --> 00:24:06.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, congratulations.

392
00:24:07.014 --> 00:24:08.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've just saved our lives.

393
00:24:09.614 --> 00:24:12.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And murdered loyal servants
of the Dominion.

394
00:24:13.252 --> 00:24:15.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
May the Founders forgive me.

395
00:24:18.771 --> 00:24:20.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Has it ever occurred to you

396
00:24:20.291 --> 00:24:22.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the reason you believe
the Founders are Gods

397
00:24:23.010 --> 00:24:25.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is because that's what they want
you to believe?

398
00:24:25.688 --> 00:24:28.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That they built it into your genetic code?

399
00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:31.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course they did.
That's what Gods do.

400
00:24:31.407 --> 00:24:35.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After all, why be a God if there's no one
to worship you.

401
00:24:45.443 --> 00:24:47.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom, where's Nog?

402
00:24:47.282 --> 00:24:50.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know, Chief. Nog left the station
a couple of hours ago in a runabout.

403
00:24:51.161 --> 00:24:52.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Who gave him permission
to use a runabout?

404
00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:53.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You did.

405
00:24:53.960 --> 00:24:57.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh! I never should have given
him my authorization code.

406
00:24:58.559 --> 00:24:59.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did he say when he'd be back?

407
00:24:59.919 --> 00:25:00.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not to me.

408
00:25:01.158 --> 00:25:02.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could he do this to me?

409
00:25:03.717 --> 00:25:06.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How could he leave me adrift
mid-river without a paddle?

410
00:25:06.836 --> 00:25:08.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What river would that be?

411
00:25:08.636 --> 00:25:11.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, the Great Material Continuum.

412
00:25:11.355 --> 00:25:14.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, that river.
It can be very treacherous.

413
00:25:14.914 --> 00:25:16.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me about it.

414
00:25:16.794 --> 00:25:20.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suppose the good news is, with Nog gone,
nothing else can go missing.

415
00:25:22.392 --> 00:25:25.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are my cases of bloodwine?

416
00:25:25.431 --> 00:25:26.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

417
00:25:27.351 --> 00:25:30.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I do not know, General,
but I promise you I will find out.

418
00:25:30.829 --> 00:25:32.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( snarling growl )

419
00:25:32.909 --> 00:25:34.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( kicks crate )

420
00:25:38.347 --> 00:25:39.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAMAR: I don't understand it.

421
00:25:39.746 --> 00:25:41.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How could a runabout destroy
a Jem'Hadar fighter?

422
00:25:42.201 --> 00:25:44.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Isn't it obvious?
My predecessor must have helped Odo

423
00:25:44.985 --> 00:25:46.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
get past the ship's defenses.

424
00:25:46.584 --> 00:25:48.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Then how do we stop them?
-How else? Send more ships.

425
00:25:48.824 --> 00:25:52.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Send a whole battalion if necessary
from our base at Olmerak.

426
00:25:52.976 --> 00:25:53.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Consider it done.

427
00:25:54.542 --> 00:25:56.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember to tell them to fire on sight.

428
00:25:57.181 --> 00:25:58.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
FEMALE SHAPE-SHIFTER: Fire at whom?

429
00:26:00.260 --> 00:26:03.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Founder, how may I serve you?

430
00:26:03.859 --> 00:26:06.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By answering my question.

431
00:26:06.419 --> 00:26:10.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We spotted a Federation runabout spying
on our base in the Olmerak system.

432
00:26:10.977 --> 00:26:13.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Surely one ship
shouldn't be much of a threat.

433
00:26:13.576 --> 00:26:15.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll have it destroyed within the hour.

434
00:26:16.615 --> 00:26:18.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling all right?

435
00:26:19.015 --> 00:26:20.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why do you ask?

436
00:26:21.491 --> 00:26:22.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your face.

437
00:26:27.652 --> 00:26:29.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm fine.

438
00:26:29.852 --> 00:26:31.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But from now on,
I want the temperature in these rooms

439
00:26:31.930 --> 00:26:33.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
lowered by 15 degrees.

440
00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:37.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I do not share
the Cardassians' love of heat.

441
00:26:37.440 --> 00:26:39.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nor do I. Lower the temperature.

442
00:26:39.849 --> 00:26:41.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As you wish.

443
00:26:41.968 --> 00:26:43.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything else I can do for you?

444
00:26:44.007 --> 00:26:46.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you located Weyoun 6?

445
00:26:46.447 --> 00:26:49.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's only a matter of time.
-So you keep saying.

446
00:26:49.886 --> 00:26:52.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assure you, Founder,
he will be dealt with.

447
00:27:00.042 --> 00:27:03.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you notice her face?
How parched it looked?

448
00:27:03.881 --> 00:27:06.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You heard her. These rooms are too hot.

449
00:27:06.750 --> 00:27:09.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wonder.
I'm telling you she's not well.

450
00:27:09.639 --> 00:27:12.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's not the Founder
you should be worried about.

451
00:27:12.439 --> 00:27:16.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Contact Olmerak and order those ships
to intercept the runabout.

452
00:27:26.714 --> 00:27:28.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mmm... mmm-mmm.

453
00:27:34.265 --> 00:27:35.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( clatters )

454
00:27:36.991 --> 00:27:37.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

455
00:27:50.420 --> 00:27:50.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was filling.

456
00:27:52.546 --> 00:27:53.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would hope so.

457
00:27:54.162 --> 00:27:55.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've sampled
the replicator's entire menu.

458
00:27:56.544 --> 00:27:59.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I enjoyed the different... textures.

459
00:28:04.320 --> 00:28:05.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean tastes, don't you?

460
00:28:03.462 --> 00:28:06.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not at all. The Vorta's sense of taste
is quite limited.

461
00:28:06.381 --> 00:28:08.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
About the only foods we really enjoy

462
00:28:08.981 --> 00:28:10.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are <i>kava </i>nuts and rippleberries.

463
00:28:10.860 --> 00:28:12.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. I take it

464
00:28:13.059 --> 00:28:16.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this is also the result
of your genetic programming?

465
00:28:16.498 --> 00:28:19.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the Founder's way of making sure
we remember our past.

466
00:28:21.096 --> 00:28:24.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You must know the story
of how the Founders created the Vorta?

467
00:28:25.375 --> 00:28:26.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) No.

468
00:28:27.855 --> 00:28:31.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have the feeling
you're going to tell me all about it.

469
00:28:34.333 --> 00:28:38.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Vorta used to be quite different
from what we are today.

470
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:43.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We were forest dwellers, small, timid,
ape-like creatures,

471
00:28:43.849 --> 00:28:45.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
living in hollowed-out trees.

472
00:28:45.409 --> 00:28:49.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eating nuts and berries.
And living in fear of the many predators

473
00:28:50.048 --> 00:28:51.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that would hunt us for food.

474
00:28:52.087 --> 00:28:55.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One day, a wounded changeling
came stumbling through the forest,

475
00:28:55.846 --> 00:28:57.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
fleeing from a mob of angry solids.

476
00:28:57.926 --> 00:29:01.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why were they chasing him?
-What does it matter?

477
00:29:01.804 --> 00:29:04.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Solids have always feared
and mistrusted shape-shifters.

478
00:29:04.283 --> 00:29:05.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know that.

479
00:29:06.164 --> 00:29:10.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, a family of Vorta
hid the changeling from his pursuers,

480
00:29:11.441 --> 00:29:13.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and in exchange for saving his life,

481
00:29:13.881 --> 00:29:17.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the changeling promised
the Vorta that one day

482
00:29:17.906 --> 00:29:21.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we would be transformed
into powerful beings,

483
00:29:22.158 --> 00:29:27.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that we would become an important part
of a great new empire

484
00:29:27.117 --> 00:29:32.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-that would stretch across the galaxy.
-And the changeling kept his word?

485
00:29:32.356 --> 00:29:34.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right. Imagine, Odo,

486
00:29:35.434 --> 00:29:39.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my people were once little more than apes,
and look at us now.

487
00:29:40.752 --> 00:29:42.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look at what you've done for us.

488
00:29:45.823 --> 00:29:48.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the story were true,
it would at least prove

489
00:29:48.391 --> 00:29:52.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that my people are capable
of generosity and kindness.

490
00:29:56.148 --> 00:29:58.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You care about your people
very much, don't you, Odo,

491
00:29:59.307 --> 00:30:01.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in spite of all that's happened
between you?

492
00:30:03.426 --> 00:30:06.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe I do,
but that doesn't change the fact

493
00:30:06.785 --> 00:30:09.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that they're responsible for a war
that's killed millions.

494
00:30:11.104 --> 00:30:14.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo, there's something you need to know.

495
00:30:16.781 --> 00:30:20.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A sickness has spread
throughout the Great Link.

496
00:30:20.780 --> 00:30:21.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Founders...

497
00:30:23.940 --> 00:30:25.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are dying.

498
00:30:37.096 --> 00:30:39.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was summoned to a meeting
by the female changeling.

499
00:30:39.735 --> 00:30:42.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She wanted to discuss
troop deployments with me,

500
00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:44.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and suddenly, her hands began to...

501
00:30:45.413 --> 00:30:47.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shrivel.

502
00:30:47.333 --> 00:30:49.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It lasted only a second or two,

503
00:30:49.892 --> 00:30:52.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but over the last few weeks
it's happened a number of times.

504
00:30:53.091 --> 00:30:55.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's like she's... withering.

505
00:30:58.049 --> 00:31:02.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you're sure
the other changelings are also infected?

506
00:31:02.768 --> 00:31:06.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She said the entire Link
is suffering from the disease.

507
00:31:11.372 --> 00:31:12.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everyone but me.

508
00:31:13.165 --> 00:31:16.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they're unable to find a cure,
you'll be the last of your kind.

509
00:31:22.332 --> 00:31:26.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why didn't you tell me this earlier?
Because I knew how much it would hurt you.

510
00:31:26.321 --> 00:31:32.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry to bring you such sad news,
but at least you're not infected.

511
00:31:33.039 --> 00:31:35.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion will survive.

512
00:31:37.238 --> 00:31:38.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

513
00:31:38.797 --> 00:31:42.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Think about it, Odo.
You have an opportunity

514
00:31:43.196 --> 00:31:46.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to rectify the mistakes
your people have made.

515
00:31:46.275 --> 00:31:51.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To build a new Dominion
based on cooperation, not conquest,

516
00:31:51.273 --> 00:31:56.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on peace, not war,
a new order under your leadership.

517
00:31:58.232 --> 00:32:01.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what's your role going
to be in this "new order"?

518
00:32:02.910 --> 00:32:05.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever you want it to be.

519
00:32:06.109 --> 00:32:08.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish only to serve you.

520
00:32:11.068 --> 00:32:13.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( beeping )
( alarm blaring )

521
00:32:13.147 --> 00:32:14.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

522
00:32:14.947 --> 00:32:17.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you can start
by telling me how one runabout

523
00:32:17.305 --> 00:32:20.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is going to survive an assault
by four Jem'Hadar ships.

524
00:32:20.345 --> 00:32:22.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sure you'll think of something.

525
00:32:30.542 --> 00:32:32.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a Kuiper belt not far from here.

526
00:32:32.541 --> 00:32:35.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We might be able to hide
among the comet fragments.

527
00:32:35.900 --> 00:32:39.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we don't have much time.
They're closing fast.

528
00:32:56.894 --> 00:32:59.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These comet fragments
are nothing but huge chunks of ice.

529
00:32:59.733 --> 00:33:02.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Jem'Hadar will have
no trouble finding us.

530
00:33:03.292 --> 00:33:04.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if we become the ice.

531
00:33:26.285 --> 00:33:28.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( equipment powering down )

532
00:33:29.951 --> 00:33:31.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, with the power off

533
00:33:31.363 --> 00:33:33.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and the runabout in thermal
contact with the ice,

534
00:33:33.963 --> 00:33:36.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we won't generate enough
of an energy signature

535
00:33:36.402 --> 00:33:38.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for their sensors to read.

536
00:33:38.081 --> 00:33:40.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"We become the ice."

537
00:33:42.313 --> 00:33:44.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only a God could think of such a thing.

538
00:33:44.359 --> 00:33:46.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, let's just hope the Jem'Hadar
give up their search

539
00:33:46.559 --> 00:33:48.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before we freeze to death.

540
00:33:48.159 --> 00:33:50.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My faith will keep me warm.

541
00:33:50.198 --> 00:33:52.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. Perhaps, but in an hour,

542
00:33:53.077 --> 00:33:57.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you may want to trade
in that faith for a thermal blanket.

543
00:34:01.075 --> 00:34:02.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

544
00:34:02.995 --> 00:34:03.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's white.

545
00:34:04.474 --> 00:34:05.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know it's white.

546
00:34:05.833 --> 00:34:07.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to paint it.

547
00:34:08.112 --> 00:34:09.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the wrong shape.

548
00:34:10.392 --> 00:34:12.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the wrong height, the wrong width.

549
00:34:13.271 --> 00:34:14.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Other than that, it's perfect.

550
00:34:15.270 --> 00:34:17.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Captain'll never suspect
you switched desks on him.

551
00:34:17.829 --> 00:34:21.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Julian, I need help, not sarcasm.

552
00:34:21.788 --> 00:34:23.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid Nog's the only one
who can help you now.

553
00:34:23.748 --> 00:34:26.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If he gets back to the station
before the Captain does.

554
00:34:26.987 --> 00:34:30.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe he's not coming back.
Maybe he's decided to make a run for it.

555
00:34:32.985 --> 00:34:34.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That isn't the Captain's desk.

556
00:34:34.345 --> 00:34:35.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's going to paint it.

557
00:34:35.984 --> 00:34:37.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get it out of here!

558
00:34:38.263 --> 00:34:39.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I help you, General?

559
00:34:39.343 --> 00:34:41.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No... but he can!

560
00:34:44.462 --> 00:34:45.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: Bloodwine?

561
00:34:45.902 --> 00:34:51.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sixteen cases... sent to me by my wife.
Now, where are they?

562
00:34:51.780 --> 00:34:55.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, how... how should I know?
-You authorized their removal.

563
00:34:55.698 --> 00:34:59.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That is your authorization code,
is it not?

564
00:34:59.178 --> 00:34:59.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog.

565
00:35:00.457 --> 00:35:01.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief...

566
00:35:03.056 --> 00:35:07.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want that bloodwine
back here by tomorrow.

567
00:35:07.935 --> 00:35:09.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Understood?

568
00:35:13.892 --> 00:35:17.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( shivering )

569
00:35:17.772 --> 00:35:19.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo...

570
00:35:19.451 --> 00:35:22.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when you said
you were cutting power to all systems,

571
00:35:23.051 --> 00:35:24.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
did that include life-support?

572
00:35:25.849 --> 00:35:27.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid so.

573
00:35:27.529 --> 00:35:29.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. That explains it.

574
00:35:29.888 --> 00:35:30.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Explains what?

575
00:35:30.887 --> 00:35:33.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why I'm having trouble breathing.

576
00:35:35.807 --> 00:35:39.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should have enough oxygen left
for another three hours.

577
00:35:39.765 --> 00:35:42.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, by then,
we will have probably frozen to death.

578
00:35:43.524 --> 00:35:45.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you can't die.

579
00:35:45.563 --> 00:35:48.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have to survive
to rebuild the Dominion.

580
00:35:50.322 --> 00:35:52.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( explosion )

581
00:35:52.522 --> 00:35:53.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They found us.

582
00:36:03.878 --> 00:36:06.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What do we do now?
-We can't stay here.

583
00:36:06.397 --> 00:36:09.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're not going to try
to outrun those ships, are you?

584
00:36:09.117 --> 00:36:10.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What choice do we have?

585
00:36:36.428 --> 00:36:39.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're on fire.
-There's an extinguisher behind you.

586
00:36:41.867 --> 00:36:43.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you waiting for?

587
00:36:45.745 --> 00:36:47.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I live only to serve you.

588
00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:04.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( com console beeping )

589
00:37:04.900 --> 00:37:07.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are you doing? Why have you activated
the com system?

590
00:37:10.098 --> 00:37:12.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right. Call off those ships.

591
00:37:12.137 --> 00:37:13.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why should I? </i>

592
00:37:13.337 --> 00:37:15.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because you don't need
them anymore.

593
00:37:19.135 --> 00:37:21.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm glad to see </i>
<i>you've come to your senses.</i>

594
00:37:23.295 --> 00:37:25.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What have you done?

595
00:37:24.734 --> 00:37:27.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've saved your life,
and the Dominion's as well.

596
00:37:27.972 --> 00:37:30.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>He's activated his termination implant</i>

597
00:37:30.172 --> 00:37:33.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and proven himself </i>
<i>to be a worthy Vorta at last.</i>

598
00:37:33.172 --> 00:37:35.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I obey the Founders in all things.

599
00:37:38.409 --> 00:37:40.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now call off those ships!

600
00:37:40.949 --> 00:37:44.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't know what he told Odo.
He may have revealed important tactical...

601
00:37:43.728 --> 00:37:45.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a risk we'll just have to take.

602
00:37:45.847 --> 00:37:47.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

603
00:37:47.287 --> 00:37:49.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've ordered the Jem'Hadar
to break off the attack.

604
00:37:50.486 --> 00:37:53.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I see your runabout has suffered
some battle damage.

605
00:37:53.125 --> 00:37:54.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Will you require any further assistance?

606
00:37:54.965 --> 00:37:56.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think you've done enough!

607
00:37:56.844 --> 00:38:01.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I sincerely regret any... inconvenience</i>
<i>we may have caused you, Odo.</i>

608
00:38:02.522 --> 00:38:07.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Please have a safe and pleasant journey</i>
<i>back to Deep Space 9.</i>

609
00:38:08.921 --> 00:38:12.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They say voluntary termination
is quick and painless.

610
00:38:12.799 --> 00:38:14.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid it's not true.

611
00:38:14.239 --> 00:38:15.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll get you a pain suppresser.

612
00:38:15.894 --> 00:38:19.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That won't be necessary,
but there is one thing you can do for me.

613
00:38:19.358 --> 00:38:20.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

614
00:38:20.677 --> 00:38:22.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give me your blessing.

615
00:38:24.156 --> 00:38:25.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I can't.

616
00:38:25.116 --> 00:38:26.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, Odo.

617
00:38:26.995 --> 00:38:29.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell me I haven't failed,
that I've served you well.

618
00:38:29.954 --> 00:38:32.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have,
and for that you have my gratitude...

619
00:38:35.793 --> 00:38:38.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and... my blessing.

620
00:39:05.704 --> 00:39:07.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, the Captain's back.

621
00:39:07.703 --> 00:39:09.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know. He sent for me.

622
00:39:09.383 --> 00:39:10.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

623
00:39:11.382 --> 00:39:12.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

624
00:39:16.340 --> 00:39:17.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, Chief.

625
00:39:18.339 --> 00:39:19.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain, your desk...

626
00:39:19.899 --> 00:39:21.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it looks nice, doesn't it?

627
00:39:21.859 --> 00:39:24.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I came in this morning and found
Ensign Nog polishing it.

628
00:39:24.689 --> 00:39:26.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was looking a little dull.

629
00:39:27.484 --> 00:39:29.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, here is the maintenance request
from the <i>Gettysburg.</i>

630
00:39:29.896 --> 00:39:31.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should be docking here later today.

631
00:39:32.215 --> 00:39:33.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That'll be all.

632
00:39:34.295 --> 00:39:35.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

633
00:39:35.934 --> 00:39:37.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, about the stabilizer...

634
00:39:37.734 --> 00:39:40.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain, I-I can explain.
-SISKO: Don't bother.

635
00:39:40.253 --> 00:39:43.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ensign Nog tells me you were able
to get a hold of one this morning.

636
00:39:44.492 --> 00:39:45.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was?

637
00:39:45.931 --> 00:39:46.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, I was.

638
00:39:47.011 --> 00:39:48.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long before you can have it on line?

639
00:39:49.810 --> 00:39:51.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Um... eight hours.

640
00:39:51.850 --> 00:39:54.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I plan to take the <i>Defiant</i>
out on patrol in two.

641
00:39:54.889 --> 00:39:56.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Two it is, sir.

642
00:39:58.768 --> 00:40:00.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how you did it, Nog.

643
00:40:00.979 --> 00:40:03.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never lost faith
in the Great Material Continuum.

644
00:40:03.766 --> 00:40:05.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, like you say, the River will provide.

645
00:40:05.486 --> 00:40:06.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief!

646
00:40:07.005 --> 00:40:09.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The waters just got choppy again.

647
00:40:10.124 --> 00:40:11.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want you to have this.

648
00:40:11.563 --> 00:40:13.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Consider it an apology.

649
00:40:13.363 --> 00:40:14.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... you found the bloodwine?

650
00:40:14.962 --> 00:40:17.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not exactly. Ensign Nog
returned from his trip

651
00:40:18.330 --> 00:40:22.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with 16 cases of 2309,
a very good year.

652
00:40:22.441 --> 00:40:25.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An even better vintage
than the one my wife sent me.

653
00:40:25.906 --> 00:40:27.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

654
00:40:27.359 --> 00:40:29.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm, uh...
I'm glad you approve.

655
00:40:30.289 --> 00:40:31.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And remember,

656
00:40:31.238 --> 00:40:32.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
any time you're shopping
for wines or spirits,

657
00:40:33.038 --> 00:40:34.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my Cousin Gant is the man to see.

658
00:40:34.757 --> 00:40:36.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will keep that in mind.

659
00:40:38.715 --> 00:40:39.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your Cousin Gant?

660
00:40:40.036 --> 00:40:42.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just another sailor on the Great River.
-Ah...

661
00:40:42.114 --> 00:40:45.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By the way, Gant mentioned
he's got ten cases of Saurian brandy.

662
00:40:46.248 --> 00:40:46.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the Captain's favorite, you know.

663
00:41:01.541 --> 00:41:02.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Level 5.

664
00:41:02.641 --> 00:41:03.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does he want for them?

665
00:40:53.391 --> 00:40:56.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think I'll ever forget
the look on his face when he died.

666
00:40:59.769 --> 00:41:01.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He seemed so... content.

667
00:40:46.670 --> 00:40:59.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The last thing he saw

668
00:40:57.862 --> 00:41:02.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was one of his Gods smiling at him.
If you ask me, he was a lucky man.

669
00:41:04.610 --> 00:41:05.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys, please.

670
00:41:05.420 --> 00:41:07.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, listen to me.

671
00:41:08.139 --> 00:41:09.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know to Starfleet

672
00:41:09.819 --> 00:41:12.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Prophets are nothing
more than wormhole aliens,

673
00:41:13.578 --> 00:41:16.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but to me, they're Gods.

674
00:41:17.569 --> 00:41:19.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
KIRA: I can't prove it.
Then, again, I don't have to,

675
00:41:20.559 --> 00:41:22.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
because my faith in them is enough,

676
00:41:22.975 --> 00:41:27.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just as Weyoun's faith in you...
was enough for him.

677
00:41:30.453 --> 00:41:32.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, now it appears that the Vorta

678
00:41:32.452 --> 00:41:35.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
may have to learn
to get along without their Gods.

679
00:41:35.651 --> 00:41:36.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

680
00:41:39.570 --> 00:41:41.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're worried about your people.

681
00:41:44.809 --> 00:41:48.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The changelings are dying,
and I can't help them.

682
00:41:49.367 --> 00:41:53.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They're the enemy.
-A very dangerous enemy.

683
00:41:53.846 --> 00:41:55.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now more than ever,

684
00:41:55.605 --> 00:41:57.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
because they're all so desperate.

685
00:41:57.845 --> 00:42:00.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) This isn't easy for you,

686
00:42:00.404 --> 00:42:02.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you have to remember
they started this war.

687
00:42:02.643 --> 00:42:03.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You didn't.

688
00:42:04.242 --> 00:42:05.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's true...

689
00:42:07.162 --> 00:42:08.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I know now

690
00:42:09.161 --> 00:42:12.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
whichever side wins,
one thing is certain...

691
00:42:14.359 --> 00:42:16.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to lose.

